The '''2000 Stanley Cup playoffs''', the championship of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL), began in April, and concluded in June. The sixteen teams that qualified, eight from each conference, played [[Playoff format#Best-of-seven playoff|best-of-7 series]] for conference quarterfinals, semifinals and championships, and then the conference champions  played a best-of-7 series for the [[Stanley Cup]]. 

The playoffs ended when the [[New Jersey Devils]] defeated the reigning champions the [[Dallas Stars]] in a six game series to win their second [[Stanley Cup]] title in their history. Devils defenseman [[Scott Stevens]] was awarded the [[Conn Smythe Trophy]] as the MVP of the playoffs.

For the first time in history ''both'' the [[Boston Bruins]] and the [[Montreal Canadiens]] missed the playoffs in the same season.

As of 2011, this is the most recent time the [[Florida Panthers]] made the playoffs.

